{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c3a383ee-138e-4793-bb9d-f89f73f2ad4b","content":"### 3. Create the GitHub environment\n\nIn your repo, go to **Settings → Environments → New environment** and create one named `nuget`.\n\n---\n\n**How it works:** When the workflow runs, the `id-token: write` permission lets the runner obtain an OIDC token. NuGet.org validates that token against your trusted publisher registration (matching repo owner, name, workflow, and environment) — no API key needed.\n\n**To publish:** push a tag like `git tag v1.0.0 && git push --tags`.\n\nThe workflow is at `.github/workflows/publish.yml`. Want me to adjust the .NET version, trigger, or project path?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d7563308-d4f5-4e9a-b4a4-d98bb2b83595","outputTokens":153,"requestId":"1408:235A82:1B2CF77:1E41A6A:69FA9069"},"id":"634e5e62-fc63-4bb3-884f-1f44acf3f81d","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:50:55.571Z","parentId":"6e8ca46e-e4fa-409a-aa41-11a7a83eff23"}
